The paper discusses a new technique for minimizing the number of neurons in a random recurrent neural network for time series prediction. This falls under the category of neural networks (cs.NE) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses feature extraction, which is a common topic in artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The use of a hybrid architecture with external memory suggests a focus on control systems (cs.SY) and information theory (cs.IT).
